        <p>It depends on the number of authors. If the source has one to six authors, list all of them. If the source has seven or more authors, list only the first three authors, followed by 'et al.' (which means 'and others').</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How are journal titles formatted in AMA style?</summary>
        <p>In AMA style, journal titles are abbreviated according to the rules of the National Library of Medicine (NLM) and are italicized. You should not spell out the full name of the journal if an established abbreviation exists.</p>
      </details>
